# Priority-Based CPU Scheduling in xv6

##  Project Description
This project is an extension of the xv6 operating system where a **priority-based CPU scheduling algorithm** is implemented.

By default, xv6 uses a Round Robin scheduler, where all processes are given equal CPU time. In this project, the scheduler is modified to select processes based on their **priority**, allowing higher-priority processes to execute more frequently.

---

##  Objective
The objective of this project is to understand and implement CPU scheduling at the kernel level by modifying the xv6 operating system.

---

##  Features
- Added a **priority field** to each process
- Modified scheduler to choose **highest priority RUNNABLE process**
- Implemented new system call:
  
  `setpriority(pid, priority)`

- Created a user-level command to change priority dynamically
- Verified scheduling using multiple processes

---

##  Environment
- xv6 (RISC-V)
- QEMU emulator
- RISC-V GCC toolchain
- macOS/Linux terminal

---

